  "texts": [
    "It is evident from the results that the proposed model outperformed other models, and Alexnet was found to be the second-best performer in all three cases because it uses a k-means smote sampling technique to balance the data.",
    "However, GRU, performs the least well among the classifiers, with an accuracy of 74.98% at a 50% training ratio.",
    "This is because GRU does not capture long-term dependencies from the huge time series data since it is based on the probability notion and employs neural network theory.",
    "Furthermore, the training using the majority of class samples makes it biased when identifying genuine incidents of electricity theft.",
    "As a result, GRU is unable to classify the vastly unbalanced dataset accurately."
